5ad264f5c9885e4adbd2c31c.name: Kung Pao Chicken
5ad264f5c9885e4adbd2c31c.description: Kung Pao chicken also transcribed as Gong Bao or Kung Po, is a spicy, stir-fried Chinese dish made with chicken, peanuts, vegetables, and chili peppers. The classic dish in Sichuan cuisine originated in the Sichuan Province of south-western China and includes Sichuan peppercorns.

5ac8d81e846d7ab285b29546.name: Fish Filets
5ac8d81e846d7ab285b29546.description: Boiled fish is usually made from fresh grass carp, bean sprouts, pepper and other ingredients. Oil but not greasy, spicy but not dry, hemp without bitter, tender and tender is its characteristic.

5ad229921e96b547b4a9684e.name: Dumpling
5ad229921e96b547b4a9684e.description: The dumpling is sometimes called a shrimp bonnet for its pleated shape. This dish is often served together with siumaai.
